18/11/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The European Commission and the OSCE signed an agreement Wednesday (17 November) on launching a joint electoral reform project in Albania. It envisions improving the country's voter register via a public awareness campaign, staff training and establishment of an experts' network. 
In other news Wednesday, Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano met with German Interior Minister Otto Schily in Tirana. Schily pledged Berlin's support for the new anti-trafficking centre in Vlora that opened last month. (ATA, OSCE press release - 17/11/04) 
